    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 11.86,
      "end": 15.68,
      "text": "Recorded by Christine Doer, the known as Asa, Florida.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 17.54,
      "end": 21.84,
      "text": "Asap's fables, the sheep, the wolf, and the stag.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 23.1,
      "end": 28.8,
      "text": "A stag once asked a sheep to lend him a measure of wheat, saying that his friend the wolf",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 28.8,
      "end": 30.1,
      "text": "would be his surety.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 30.9,
      "end": 36.3,
      "text": "The sheep, however, was afraid that they meant to cheat her, so she excused herself, saying,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 36.98,
      "end": 42.0,
      "text": "the wolf is in the habit of seizing what he wants and running off with it without paying.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 42.9,
      "end": 45.24,
      "text": "And you too can run much faster than I.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 45.94,
      "end": 50.9,
      "text": "So how shall I be able to come up with either of you when the debt falls due?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 52.04,
      "end": 54.4,
      "text": "Two blacks do not make a white.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 56.46,
      "end": 60.54,
      "text": "End of the sheep, the wolf, and the stag.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
